FBIS4-2310 "drchi068_k_94001" FBIS-CHI-94-068 Daily Report 8 Apr 1994 NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political & Social Beijing Police Arrest Dissident Xu Wenli Beijing Police Arrest Dissident Xu Wenli 3d Action in Week HK0804084694 Hong Kong AFP in English 0826 GMT 8 April 94 HK0804084694 Hong Kong AFP English BFN [Text] Beijing, April 8 (AFP)--Chinese dissident Xu Wenli was detained by police Friday, his wife said, in the third such action against pro-democracy activists in a week. Xu was picked up by police on Thursday then returned home around midnight, but was detained again on Friday, the wife, Kang Tong, said. Xu, 49, is a former activist in the 1978-79 pro-democracy movement who was freed last year after 12 years in jail. In the past week, China's most famous dissident, Wei Jingsheng, and his secretary, Tong Yi, have also been detained.
